<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1830,2035]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[327,464,1830,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[240,1347,518,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[240,1347,517,1899]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Abdominal sternites VII – VIII of Smilax Laporte. 13. Smilax deneinephyto Chatzimanolis. 14. Smilax pilosa (F.). 15. Smilax kuntzeni (Scheerpeltz). 16. Smilax lynchi (Bruch). Not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/268258/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">Figs. 13–16</figureCitation>
) with paired protergal glands present; abdominal terga III–V curved (arc-like) ridge and without accessory basal lines. Abdominal sternite VII in males without porose structure but with modified (various degrees of emargination) posterior margin; abdominal sternite VIII in males with U or V-shaped emargination. Abdominal sternite IX with deep V-shaped emargination posteriorly. Abdomen with small uniform dense punctures; each segment (ventral and dorsal) with row of larger setiferous punctures each giving rise to large dark macrosetae (usually 4–6 per segment).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="288">
Male and female genitalia typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[663,825,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Xanthopygina">Xanthopygina</taxonomicName>
; spermatheca not sclerotized; aedeagus smaller in comparison to other genera in 
<taxonomicName box="[498,660,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Xanthopygina">Xanthopygina</taxonomicName>
; paramere in lateral view with enlarged ventral projection; paramere much shorter than median lobe.
</paragraph>
